cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.LT, cs.SE, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a likely category as the paper discusses nominal logic and its application to process calculi. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also a likely category as the paper deals with the operational semantics of process calculi. 
- cs.LT (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper introduces rule formats for the specifications of nominal residual transition systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper deals with the specification and semantics of software systems. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is another possible category as the paper deals with the formal specification of process calculi.
